  "description": "<p><ul><li><p>Perform general administrative and operational duties</p></li><li><p>Check, process, and upload insurance policies and related documents</p></li><li><p>Handle high-volume data entry and documentation</p></li><li><p>Maintain proper filing and records management</p></li><li><p>Support claims documentation and administrative processes</p></li><li><p>Assist with invoice preparation and data entry</p></li><li><p>Follow up on work orders and required documents</p></li><li><p>Carry out ad-hoc tasks assigned by supervisors</p></li></ul></p><p><strong>Requirements:</strong><br /></p><p><ul><li><p>Diploma qualification or equivalent</p></li><li><p>Strong willingness to learn and take initiative</p></li><li><p>Good communication and interpersonal skills</p></li><li><p>Proficient in Microsoft Office applications</p></li></ul></p><p>Interested applicants for the above advertised position(s), please kindly email an updated copy of your resume to: <strong>gs1@talenttradersg.com</strong><br /></p><p>EA License No.: 13C6305</p><p>Reg. No.: R23117344 (Tiong Tian Ho)<br /></p><p>For candidate who applied for the advertised position is deemed to have consented to us that we may collect, use or disclose your personal information for purpose in connection with the services provided by us.</p><p><br /><br /></p>",
